Tekla Griebel was born in Randers, Denmark, the daughter of Theodor Johan Heinrich Griebel (1829–1900) and teacher Camilla Joachimine Andresen (1829–91).
However, she was more interested in music, and in 1886 she wrote her first opera Don Juan de Marana (eventually performed in 1931).
